      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/60",
      "text": [
        " اَلضُّرُوعِ فَقَالَ \"لاَ إِلاَّ أَنْ يَحْلُبَ لَكَ مِنْهُ سُكُرُّجَةً فَتَقُولُ أَشْتَرِي مِنْكَ هَذَا اَللَّبَنَ اَلَّذِي فِي اَلسُّكُرُّجَةِ وَ مَا فِي ضُرُوعِهَا بِثَمَنٍ مُسَمًّى فَإِنْ لَمْ يَكُنْ فِي اَلضُّرُوعِ شَيْءٌ كَانَ فِيمَا فِي اَلسُّكُرُّجَةِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3831 - Samaah asked him about purchasing milk while it is still in the udders.\nImam (as) said: \"No, unless he milks some of it into a small vessel (sukurjah) for you, and then you say, 'I purchase from you this milk that is in the vessel and what is in its udders for a specified price.' If there is nothing in the udders, then the sale applies to what is in the vessel.\""
        ]
      }
    },
    "verse_translations": [
